  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given a string **S** and **N** queries. Each query is defined by two integers - **Li** and **Pi**. Count the number of strings of the length **Li** that occur **exactly Pi** times (as the consecutive substrings) in the string **S**.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **|S|** ≤ **50**, **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **100** : 13 points.",
      "**1** ≤ **|S|** ≤ **1000**, **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **10000** : 27 points.",
      "**1** ≤ **|S|** ≤ **200000**, **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **500000** : 60 points.",
      "**1** ≤ **Li**, **Pi** ≤ **N**",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "abacaba",
      "1",
      "3 2",
      "**Output:**",
      "1",
      "&nbsp;",
      "ExplanationThe only such string is **aba**."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The first line of input contains the string **S**.\n\n\nThe second line of input contains the integer **N** - the number of queries.\n\nThen there are **N** lines, the **i**-th one contains numbers **Li** and **Pi** for the **i**-th query.",
    "outputFormat": "For each query output the answer at the corresponding line of the output.",
